lass=\"sortbottom\"\n|colspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| <small>Latest update: 31 March 2020 (source: [http://covid19.sante.gov.dz/carte/ covid19]<ref>{{cite web|title=Carte \u00e9pid\u00e9miologique|url=http://covid19.sante.gov.dz/carte/|language=fr|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref></small>)\n|}\n\n==See also== \n{{Div col}}\n*[[2020 in Algeria]]\n* [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]]\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Tunisia]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation and tourism]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Tunisia}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Morocco}}\n{{#related:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Algeria]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Algeria]]\n[[Category:2020 in Algeria]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Algeria]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Africa]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Africa]]\n", "name_user": "Walid2687", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Algeria"}
{"title_page": "Ketmen Ridge", "text_new": "{{short description|Mountain range in the Tian Shan system}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}{{more footnotes|date=March 2020}}}}\n\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name              = Ketmen Ridge\n| other_name        = \n| etymology         = \n| native_name       = \n| native_name_lang  = \n| translation       = \n| pronunciation     = \n| photo             = \n| photo_size        = \n| photo_alt         = \n| photo_caption     = \n| map               = \n| map_image         = \n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n| map_relief        = \n| map_size          = \n| location          = Uygur and Rayimbek districts, Almaty region, Republic of Kazakhstan\n| label             = \n| label_position    = \n| elevation         = \n| elevation_m       = \n| elevation_ft      = \n| elevation_ref     = \n| prominence        = \n| prominence_m      = \n| prominence_ft     = \n| prominence_ref    = \n| isolation         = \n| isolation_km      = \n| isolation_mi      = \n| isolation_ref     = \n| parent_peak       = \n| listing           = \n| range             = \n| coordinates       = \n| coordinates_ref   = \n| topo              = \n| type              = \n| age               = \n| geology           = \n| volcanic_arc      = \n| volcanic_belt     = \n| volcanic_field    = \n| volcanic_arc/belt = \n| last_eruption     = \n| first_ascent      = \n| easiest_route     = \n| normal_route      = \n| access            = \n| child             = \n| embedded          = \n}}\n\nThe Ketmen range is located at the East of the [[Trans-Ili Alatau|Zailiyskiy Alatau]] in the Northern, [[Tian Shan]]. The ridge is located on the territory of the [[Uygur District|Uyghur]] and [[Raiymbek District|Raiymbek]] districts of the [[Almaty Region|Almaty region]], also located on the territory of the [[Kazakhstan|Republic of Kazakhstan]] and the China republic. \n\nThe total length of the ridge is 310 km. The length of the ridge on the territory of Kazakhstan is 160 km. The width of the ridge reaches 40\u201350&nbsp;km. The highest point of the range is Mount Aspan (3,652 m). \n\nThe ridge is adjacent to the Kungei-AlaToo ridge in the West and the Narat ridge in the East. The Northern slopes of the ridge pass into the Ili valley. Ketmen forms the southern border of [[Zhetysu|Semirechye]]. \n\nThe ridge is composed of igneous rocks and sedimentary rocks such as effusions, granite, and limestone. The slopes of the Ridge are steep with gentle peaks below the snow line. The ridge has a permafrost zone but does not have glaciation and snowfields. There are steppes and taiga forests, which consist mainly of spruce trees and meadows in high-altitude zones. At the foot of the southern slope of the ridge, [[steppe bison]] remains have been found. \n\nThe eponymous Ketmen pass is located at an altitude of 3,040 meters above sea level in the eastern part of the mountain range. A caravan trail from the Ili valley to the Kegen-Tekes hollow is laid through the pass, which connects the Northern slope in the Ketmen gorge and southern slope of the ridge of the Shalkudysu river valley.\n\nThe Ketmen ridge is rich in terms of flora. Research has found that the Ketmen ridge consists of 1890 species of vascular plants, along with the Chinese part which are angiosperms, dicots, and monocots. 84 species from 11 genera of rust fungi were found. The largest genera found were [[Puccinia]] with 48 species, and [[Uromyces]] with 12 species.\n\n== Source and links ==\n* \u041a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0445\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d. \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0433\u0435\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 / \u0422. \u041f. \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 (\u0440\u0435\u0434.). \u2014 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f. \u2014 \u041e\u043c\u0441\u043a: \u041e\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0430\u0440\u